#: ../../../admin-guide/media/vivid.rst:1322
msgid "CEC (Consumer Electronics Control)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/vivid.rst:1324
msgid ""
"If there are HDMI inputs then a CEC adapter will be created that has the "
"same number of input ports. This is the equivalent of e.g. a TV that has "
"that number of inputs. Each HDMI output will also create a CEC adapter that "
"is hooked up to the corresponding input port, or (if there are more outputs "
"than inputs) is not hooked up at all. In other words, this is the equivalent "
"of hooking up each output device to an input port of the TV. Any remaining "
"output devices remain unconnected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/media/vivid.rst:1332
msgid ""
"The EDID that each output reads reports a unique CEC physical address that "
"is based on the physical address of the EDID of the input. So if the EDID of "
"the receiver has physical address A.B.0.0, then each output will see an EDID "
"containing physical address A.B.C.0 where C is 1 to the number of inputs. If "
"there are more outputs than inputs then the remaining outputs have a CEC "
"adapter that is disabled and reports an invalid physical address."
